The paper discusses a testing framework for distributed applications, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The framework also involves abstractions and test structure, which relates to Software Engineering (cs.SE). The use of distributed infrastructure such as PlanetLab suggests a possible category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper specifically mentions using the framework to deploy a DHT prototype, which is a common topic in Peer-to-Peer (cs.PL) research.
